Vendored library: jsPDF v3.0.4
Upstream:        https://github.com/parallax/jsPDF
License:         MIT (see LICENSE in this folder)
Bundle:          jspdf.umd.min.js (UMD, ~419 KB unminified, ~132 KB gzipped)
Source:          npm registry — `jspdf@3.0.4` tarball, `dist/jspdf.umd.min.js`

Why UMD and not the ES bundle: jsPDF's `dist/jspdf.es.min.js` contains bare
imports (`fflate`, `fast-png`, `@babel/runtime/...`) that would require their
own vendoring or an import-map entry per dep. The UMD bundle is self-contained
(it inlines those deps) and matches the loading pattern we already use for
JSZip — a `<script>` injection in the loader module that resolves once the
`globalThis.jspdf.jsPDF` global is set.

Loaded by:       `js/vendor/jspdf-loader.js`
Used by:         `js/render/pdfRenderer.js` (lazy — only when the user
                 actually clicks PDF export). The 419 KB cost is paid zero
                 times for users who never export a PDF.

Sibling vendors under this folder: `../bgremove/`, `../onnxruntime-web/`,
`../jszip.min.js`.

Upgrade path: fetch a new `jspdf-<version>.tgz` from npm, copy the new
`dist/jspdf.umd.min.js` into this folder, refresh `LICENSE`, bump the
version note in `THIRD-PARTY.md`.
